"STA.  Rours.—On coming out from Neasden station, turn leftw.rd, and follow the main road past the Old Spotted Dog tavern to a road-junction. There take the left-hand road (to Kingsbury) for three-quarters of a mile to the bridge crossing the Brent, and thence up the hill for some two hundred yards to a right-hand tarning between two farm-houses. Take this turning, and keep straight on up the lane indicated as “No Thoroughfare’’ past Kingsbury church and through a field-gate into a green enclosure, in the further left-hand corner of which is the stile of a field-"